
Overview of noun escalator

The noun escalator has 2 senses (no senses from tagged texts)
                                    
1. escalator clause, escalator -- (a clause in a contract that provides for an increase or a decrease in wages or prices or benefits etc. depending on certain conditions (as a change in the cost of living index))
2. escalator, moving staircase, moving stairway -- (a stairway whose steps move continuously on a circulating belt)
